running on linux Ubuntu 16.04:

sudo apt-get install python-virtualenv

run:
$virtualenv venv
$source venv/bin/activate
$pip install selenium

download geckodriver from https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases

$ wget geckodriver-v0.19.1-linux64.tar.gz (using linux 64 in my case)

untar it and move geckodriver into venv/bin


use your favorite text editor to modify seleniumExample.py


cp seleniumExample.py into venv

MAKE SURE your current Directory is venv so the seleniumExample.py
because in the seleniumExample.py script the script assumes the script
is in ~/CS130-cinder/testing/venv and you are currently in venv

cd into venv

run seleniumExample.py

type deactivate to exit out of venv